ANDEAN DAYBOOK: Chilean Interest Rate Decision; Peru Reports GDP

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-09-15T03:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/andean-daybook-chilean-interest-rate-decision-peru-reports-gdp.html
Chile’s central bank will keep its
benchmark  interest rate  unchanged for a third straight month,
according to all 16 economists surveyed by Bloomberg. Policy
makers will publish their decision after 5 p.m. New York time.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Peru ’s statistics agency will publish July’s gross domestic
product report after 9:30 a.m. New York time.
*Peru’s Cabinet Chief Salomon Lerner and Finance Minister Miguel
Castilla will present the government’s 2012 draft budget to
congress at 10 am New York time.  ECONOMY:
*Chilean traders and investors expect the central bank to cut
its key interest rate at least twice next year after keeping it
unchanged at 5.25 percent for the remainder of 2011, according
to the central bank’s bi-weekly survey of traders and investors.  EQUITIES:
* Chile ’s Ipsa index rose 0.5 percent to 4,052.75. The MSCI Chile
index gained 0.1 percent 2,381.09.
*Peru’s Lima General Index advanced 1 percent to 20,179.69. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 0.2 percent to 2,640.17.
* Colombia ’s IGBC index rose 0.5 percent to 13,555.00, while the
Colcap index increased 0.4 percent to 1,640.37.  MARKETS:
*Chile’s peso weakened 0.8 percent to 478.95 per  U.S. dollar 
from 475.25 per dollar Sept. 13.
*The yield on Colombia’s 10 percent benchmark bonds due in July
2024 rose three basis point, or 0.03 percentage point, to 7.33
percent. Colombia’s peso fell 0.8 percent to 1,826.75 per
dollar, from 1,813 Sept. 13.
*The yield on Peru’s benchmark 7.84 percent sol-denominated
bonds due August 2020 rose four basis points, or 0.04 percentage
points, 5.51 percent. The sol was little changed at 2,7315 from
2.7310 Sept. 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
